\description{
The eligibility of a stock/signal portfolio depends on a series of criteria, as explained in Details. Default behavior is to apply only
the \strong{Only Top Assets Rule}, in which case assets are promoted based on their signal being above a given quantile.
}
\details{
The function provides additional custom rules and also accepts user-defined rules.
\subsection{Eligibility Criteria}{

To be promoted as eligible, assets must meet one of the following criteria:
\enumerate{
\item \strong{Regular Eligibility}
\itemize{
\item \strong{Only Top Assets Rule}: Asset must be in the top quantile as specified by \code{top_quantile}.
\itemize{
\item To ignore this behavior, set \code{top_quantile} to 0.
}
\item \strong{Liquidity Floor Rule} (exclusive for stocks): must meet minimum liquidity requirements as defined by the liquidity floor rule.
}
\item OR \strong{Active Weights Constraint Policy Eligibility:}
\itemize{
\item \strong{Maximum Absolute Individual Active Weight Rule} (exlusive for stocks): Benchmark weight must exceed the maximum absolute individual active weight threshold.
}
\item OR \strong{Turnover Policy Eligibility:} (exclusive for stocks)
\itemize{
\item Stock must be in one of the buffer zones. For this to happen:
\itemize{
\item Stock must be in the top quantile buffer (\code{signal >= top_quantile_buffer}).
\item Stock must be in the pre-rebalancing portfolio.
\item Stock must meet the liquidity classification of the buffer zone.
}
}
\item OR \strong{user_defined_OR_rules Eligibility} (currently only implemented for stocks)
\item OR \strong{Group Representativeness Eligibility:}
\itemize{
\item If there are no stocks or signal portfolios in one of the groups specified in \code{concentration_constraint_policy}, a representative will be included according to the best quantile.
}
\item AND \strong{user_defined_AND_rules}
}
}

\subsection{Dominance of Rules}{
\itemize{
\item The \strong{Active Weights Constraint Policy Eligibility} is dominant; assets meeting this rule will always be eligible.
\item The \strong{Turnover Policy Eligibility} takes precedence over the \strong{Liquidity Floor Rule}; thus, a stock in the buffer zone will be included even if the liquidity floor rule suggests otherwise.
\item Assets that meet \strong{user_defined_OR_rules} will always be promoted.
\item Assets that fail to meet \strong{user_defined_AND_rules} will always be excluded.
}
}
}
